HOUSTON -- The Houston Texans' biggest star is "just a small-town kid from Wisconsin," according to J.J. Watt himself in a newly released trailer for an ESPN profile on his life. 
ESPN released a preview Tuesday for "E:60 J.J. Watt: Never Given" which shows photos and video of the defensive end from his childhood to his current days on the Texans squad. The profile is set to air on Oct. 20.
